  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Saving Brains</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heartland Alliance International (HAI) and Panzi Foundation seeks to test the efficacy of a mental health intervention on mothers who are victims of sexual violence on improved cognitive, emotional, motor and linguistic development of their infants.  The intervention will be delivered as part of a post-natal health program, using a delivery system that can be duplicated with paraprofessionals in similar low-resource environments.  Matuzo Bora Ya Watoto Wachanga is unique and innovative in that it builds on past work on depression to identify the effects of maternal sexual trauma on infants, and possible mitigating interventions focusing on depression and traumatic stress. The project will take place in conjunction with a nutritional education program and will attempt to determine whether a cognitive-behavioral intervention for victims of sexual violence has a significant and positive independent effect on brain development in infants, when offered in conjunction with standard post-natal screening and nutritional assistance programs.</narrative>
  </description>
